The paper focuses on deep transfer learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of deep networks and adaptation networks suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper applies transfer learning to computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of adversarial training and back-propagation suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also deals with natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category, as it deals with transfer learning in the context of image and text data.
